{{Infobox scientist | honorific_prefix = | name = Ewine van Dishoeck | honorific_suffix = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = EwineVanDishoeck.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Ewine van Dishoeck (2015) | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1955|06|13}} | birth_place = [[Leiden]], [[Netherlands]] | death_date = <!--{{death date and age |YYYY|MM|DD |YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)--> | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}--> | other_names = | residence = [[Leiden]], [[Netherlands]] | citizenship = | nationality = | fields = [[Astrochemistry]], [[Astronomy]], [[Chemistry]] | workplaces = | patrons = | education = | alma_mater = | thesis_title = <!--(or | thesis1_title = and | thesis2_title = )--> | thesis_url = <!--(or | thesis1_url = and | thesis2_url = )--> | thesis_year = <!--(or | thesis1_year = and | thesis2_year = )--> | doctoral_advisors = H.J. Habing, [[Alexander Dalgarno]] | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | influences = | influenced = | awards = *[[Kavli Prize for Astrophysics]], 2018 * [[James Craig Watson Medal]], 2018 * [[Albert Einstein World Award of Science]], 2015 * [[Gothenburg Lise Meitner]], 2014 * Bourke Award, 2001 *[[Spinoza Prize]], 2000 * Gold Medal of the Royal Dutch Chemical Society, 1994 | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = [[Tim de Zeeuw]] | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = http://home.strw.leidenuniv.nl/~ewine/ | footnotes = }}
'''Ewine Fleur van Dishoeck''' (born 13 June 1955 in [[Leiden]]) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[astronomer]] and [[chemist]].<ref name='cv'>{{cite web | url = http://www.strw.leidenuniv.nl/~ewine/cv.html | title = Curriculum Vitae | accessdate=2010-01-27}}</ref> She is Professor of [[Atomic and molecular astrophysics|Molecular Astrophysics]] at [[Leiden Observatory]],<ref name='cv' /><ref name='pnas'>{{Cite journal | last1 = Zagorski | first1 = N. | title = Profile of Ewine F. Van Dishoeck | doi = 10.1073/pnas.0604740103 | journal = Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences | volume = 103 | issue = 33 | pages = 12229–12231 | year = 2006 | pmid = 16894155 | pmc =1567862 |bibcode = 2006PNAS..10312229Z }}</ref> and the president of the [[International Astronomical Union]]. She is one of the pioneers of [[astrochemistry]], and her research is aimed at determination of the structure of cosmic objects using their molecular spectra.
She won the [[Kavli Prize]] for astrophysics in 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kavliprize.org/prizes-and-laureates/prizes/2018-kavli-prize-astrophysics|title=Kavli Prize for astrophysics}}</ref>. She is a member of the [[Royal Dutch Academy of Sciences]] since 2001<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.knaw.nl/en/members/members/5132 |title=Ewine van Dishoeck |publisher=[[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]] |date= |accessdate=17 July 2015}}</ref> and the U.S. [[United States National Academy of Sciences|National Academy of Sciences]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.nasonline.org/site/Dir/82755351?pg=rslts | title = National Academy of Sciences - Members Directory | accessdate=2010-01-27}}</ref> She received the [[James Craig Watson Medal]] in 2018,<ref>{{cite web|title=News from the National Academy of Sciences|url=http://www.nasonline.org/news-and-multimedia/news/2018-nas-awards-recipients.html|publisher=[[National Academy of Sciences]]|publication-date=17 January 2018|accessdate=26 May 2018}}</ref> the [[Albert Einstein World Award of Science]] in 2015,<ref>{{cite web|title=2015 World Cultural Council Awards|publisher=EurekAlert!|url=http://www.eurekalert.org/pub_releases/2015-06/ccm-2wc060815.php|publication-date=June 10, 2015|accessdate=June 10, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Einstein World Award of Science voor Ewine van Dishoeck|publisher=[[Leiden University]]|url=http://science.leidenuniv.nl/index.php/faculteit/newsitem/einstein_world_award_of_science_voor_ewine_van_dishoeck/|language=Dutch|publication-date=10 June 2015|accessdate=11 June 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612023704/http://science.leidenuniv.nl/index.php/faculteit/newsitem/einstein_world_award_of_science_voor_ewine_van_dishoeck/|archivedate=12 June 2015|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Two international awards for Ewine van Dishoeck|url=http://www.innovations-report.com/html/reports/awards-funding/two-international-awards-for-ewine-van-dishoeck.html|publisher=Innovations Report|publication-date=22 June 2015|accessdate=22 June 2015|last=Hämmerle|first=Hannelore}}</ref> the [[Gothenburg]] [[Lise Meitner]] Award in 2014,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.chalmers.se/EN/CENTRES/GPC/ACTIVITIES/LISEMEITNER/Pages/2014-Ewine-van-Dishoeck.aspx | title = Gothenburg Lise Meitner Award 2014, Ewine van Dishoeck | publisher = Gothenburg Physics Centre | accessdate=2014-09-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.astronomie.nl/#!/nova/pers/persberichten/_detail/gli/astrochemist-ewine-van-dishoeck-receives-gothenbur/ | title = Astrochemist Ewine van Dishoeck receives Gothenburg Lise Meitner Award 2014 | publisher = Astronomie.nl | date=2014-09-19 | accessdate=2014-09-19}}</ref> the [[Spinoza Prize]] in 2000,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.nwo.nl/NWOHome.nsf/pages/NWOP_5VNCW6_Eng#2000 | publisher = Netherlands Organisation for Scientific Research | title = NWO/Spinoza Prizes | accessdate = 2010-01-27 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110822072703/http://www.nwo.nl/nwohome.nsf/pages/NWOP_5VNCW6_Eng#2000 | archivedate = 2011-08-22 | df = }}</ref> the Bourke Award of the [[Royal Society of Chemistry]] (UK) in 2001<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.rsc.org/ScienceAndTechnology/Awards/BourkeAward/PreviousWinners.asp | title = RSC Bourke Award Previous Winners | accessdate=2010-01-27}}</ref> and the Gold Medal of the Royal Dutch Chemical Society in 1994. She works on [[Interstellar medium|interstellar]] [[Molecular cloud|molecule]]s; physical and [[Chemical element|chemical]] evolution during [[star formation]] and [[Planetary system|planet formation]]; [[Far infrared astronomy|submillimeter]] and mid-[[infrared astronomy]]; basic molecular processes; and the [[radiative transfer]] of line and continuum radiation.<ref name='cv' />
She was a Junior Fellow of the [[Harvard Society of Fellows]].<ref name='pnas'/>
Van Dishoeck is married to [[Tim de Zeeuw]],<ref name='pnas' /> also a professor of astronomy at Leiden University and from September 2007 to 2017, Director General of the [[European Southern Observatory]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.eso.org/public/about-eso/dg-office/index.html | title = ESO - Director General | accessdate=2010-01-27}}</ref>
